      </div>
      <div class="hard">
      <div class="hard"></div>

      <div>
        <h1 class="text">My Angels and My Demons</h1>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">Seven chimes ring from an abandoned church,<br>and a pair of angels awaken me, I open my eyes and<br>hear an old tune, that wraps me, and<br>leads me to succumb to my demons.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">They’re resolved not to leave me in peace,<br>they show me the shortest path<br>to hell. Time stops and<br>the saving angels come to me, and without asking much,</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">they switch the roles, and without visa or passport,<br>they take you<br>northward, because that's where everyone goes.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">I discover<br>that my demons are inside me, they’ve always lived<br>feeding on intrigue, hatred,<br>envy and despair, piling up for years.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">My angels are not afraid, they’ve never<br>lost a battle, I spin my siguaraya branch,<br>and my orishas, standing tall,<br>lift me up, make the inner battle<br>easier.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">The river stones<br>echo,<br>and an old man laughs staring into a bottomless pit,<br>which lives in his mind, lurking even at the death of a simple ant,</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text">reciting Neruda’s poems by heart.</p>
      </div>

